This paper deals with natural language processing and language modeling, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and language models, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of latent representations, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of discourse trees, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) for image captioning tasks.
